## Phase 4: Modern MIDI & Expression
*Objective: Future-proof synthesis and sequencing.*

### 4.1 MPE (MIDI Polyphonic Expression) Integration ✅ DONE (2026-04-27)
- **Previous State:** Standard 14-bit MIDI only; all notes shared a single pitch-bend lane; no per-note pressure or timbre routing.
- **Implementation:**
  - **`TrackCommand`**: added `MpeExpression` to the `Type` enum and a `MpePayload` POD struct (noteId, channel, pitchBendSemitones, pressure, timbre) as a zero-initialised member. `static_assert(is_trivially_copyable_v<TrackCommand>)` enforces ABI for `LockFreeQueue<TrackCommand,128>`.
  - **`MidiNote`** (`ClipData.h`): extended with `hasMpe`, `pressure`, `pitchBend`, `timbre` snapshot fields; defaults preserve full backward compatibility with all existing projects.
  - **New `MpeZoneManager`** (`Source/Core/MpeZoneManager.h`): message-thread-only class. Detects lower/upper MPE zones from RPN 0 / CC#6 messages *or* by auto-detecting simultaneous multi-channel Note Ons (permissive fallback for controllers that skip RPN). Tracks per-channel note assignments and translates PitchBend / ChannelPressure / CC74 into `TrackCommand::MpePayload`.
  - **`MainComponent`**: `mpeZone` member (message thread only) + `std::atomic<int> mpeTargetTrack{0}` (the currently selected/armed track receives live MPE). `handleIncomingMidiMessage` routes expression CCs through `mpeZone` → `commandQueue`; Note On/Off still forwarded to `midiCollector` for voice allocation.
  - **`Track::processPatternCommands`**: new `MpeExpression` branch translates payload into `juce::MidiMessage::pitchWheel` + `channelPressureChange` + `controllerEvent(74)` injected into `midiBuffer` at sample offset 0 — no heap allocation, no new thread.
  - **`WavetableSynthProcessor` / `WTVoice`**: per-voice `mpeChannel`, `mpePitchBendSemitones`, `mpePressure`, `mpeTimbre` fields; `noteOn(ch)` records the MPE channel and resets expression. `renderNextBlock` applies `bendRatio = pow(2, semitones/12)` to `baseFreq`, scales amplitude by `mpePressure` (or routes to filter cutoff), and offsets wavetable position by `mpeTimbre`. `processBlock` dispatches `isPitchWheel` / `isChannelPressure` / `isController(74)` to the matching voice by channel. `WTParams` gains `mpePressureTarget`, `mpeTimbreDepth`, `mpeBendRange` atomics (saved/loaded in `ValueTree`).
  - **`FMSynthProcessor` / `FMVoice`**: identical MPE voice-state pattern; `renderNextBlock` applies bend to `baseFreq` and pressure to output amplitude; `FMParams` gains `mpePressureTarget`, `mpeTimbreRange`, `mpeBendRange` atomics.
  - **GUI**: both `WavetableSynthComponent` and `FMSynthComponent` gain an **MPE MAPPING** panel: *Pressure →* ComboBox (Amplitude / Filter Cutoff) + *Timbre Depth* / *Bend Range* knobs (default ±48 semitones, GUI-adjustable).
  - **`PianoRollEditor`**: notes with `hasMpe == true` render in a **blue→red** gradient by pressure; a yellow **pitch-bend indicator** (line + dot) is drawn below the note block when `|pitchBend| > 0.05` semitones.
  - **XML persistence**: `WTParams` / `FMParams` MPE config saved as `mpePT` / `mpeTD` / `mpeBR` properties; `MidiNote` MPE fields deferred to the MIDI recording phase (v0.2); all existing presets and project files load without change.
  - Deferred to v0.2 (documented in `ideas_for_v0.2.md`): dedicated MPE Input Track selector (option B), real-time MIDI recording with per-note snapshot capture, manual "Set Expression…" right-click in the Piano Roll, and full FM operator-ratio timbre modulation.
- **Validation:** Build verified clean (zero errors). Manual test: connect an MPE controller (or virtual MIDI loopback), play simultaneous notes on different channels, verify per-note pitch bend on `WavetableSynth` and independent amplitude via pressure. Save/reload project; confirm MPE GUI knob values round-trip correctly.

